```

**Additional text:**
```
Click the link in your email to activate your account and access Kira. Check your spam folder if you don't see it.
```

**Button:** "Back to sign in"

### 2. emailRedirectTo URL (Auth.tsx, line 177)

```javascript
emailRedirectTo: `${window.location.origin}/auth`,
```

This is set during the `signUp` call when a user signs up with email/password on the signup form.

### 3. OAuth/Token Hash Handling (Auth.tsx, lines 14-16, 39)

**hasOAuthCallback function:**
```javascript
const hasOAuthCallback = () => {
  const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
  return params.has("code") || params.has("token_hash") || window.location.hash.includes("access_token");
};
```

**Processing state:**
```javascript
const [isProcessingOAuth, setIsProcessingOAuth] = useState(hasOAuthCallback);
```

When a user lands on `/auth` with `?token_hash=` (or `code` or `access_token`), `isProcessingOAuth` is `true`, which triggers the loading spinner (lines 278-287):

```jsx
if (isProcessingOAuth) {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-background via-bronze/5 to-background flex items-center justify-center p-4">
      <div className="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 text-center">
        <Loader2 className="w-10 h-10 animate-spin text-bronze" />
        <p className="font-poppins text-muted-foreground">Signing you in…</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 4. Navigation to /kira After Token Exchange (Auth.tsx, lines 70-77)

The `onAuthStateChange` listener handles navigation:
```javascript
supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange(async (event, session) => {
  if (event === 'SIGNED_IN' && session) {
    const { data: aalData } = await supabase.auth.mfa.getAuthenticatorAssuranceLevel();
    if (aalData?.nextLevel === "aal2" && aalData?.nextLevel !== aalData?.currentLevel) {
      navigate("/mfa-verify", { replace: true });
    } else {
      navigate("/kira", { replace: true });
    }
  }
```

After token exchange completes, Supabase fires `SIGNED_IN`, and the app navigates to `/kira` (or `/mfa-verify` if MFA is required).

### 5. Password Reset Redirect (ResetPassword.tsx, line 86)

Same mechanism: after password reset succeeds, it navigates to `/kira` directly.
